<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Communist Party Delegation Arrives in Hanoi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese Communist Party
delegation headed by Wei Jianxing, a member of the Political
Bureau of the Central Committee of Communist Party of China
(CCCPC) arrived in Hanoi Thursday on an official goodwill visit.
</P>
<P>
Wei, also a member of the Secretariat of the Political Bureau
of CCCPC, and his entourage were cordially welcomed by Pham The
Duyet, a member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of
Vietnam (CPV).
</P>
<P>
In a written speech at the airport, Wei said China and Vietnam
were good neighbors and the two peoples have a long history of
contact.
</P>
<P>
In the long-term struggle for national independence and
liberation, they had extended mutual support and sympathy and
built profound friendship.
</P>
<P>
"We are very delighted to see that recent years have seen an
all-round development in the friendly cooperative bonds between
the two parties and two countries, and an ever-increasing
expansion of contact and cooperation in various fields," Wei said.
</P>
<P>
He said he expected to meet Vietnamese leaders to have an
in-depth discussion on the relationship between the two countries
and parties as well as international and regional issues of mutual
concern.
</P>
<P>
He believed that the visit would promote mutual understanding
and further the friendly cooperation between the two countries and
parties.
</P>
<P>
Both countries were faced with the same task of developing
their economies and improving living standards and had a broad
prospect for cooperation, Wei said.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese people were willing to cooperate with the
Vietnamese people and both would learn in their pursuit of common
development and contribution to Asia's peace and stability. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
