<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0005 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Contracted Overseas Investment in China up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- China reported more than 31.7
billion US dollars in contractual overseas investment in the first
eight months of this year, up six percent from the same period of
last year, according to the latest statistics of the Ministry of
Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC).
</P>
<P>
The value of overseas investment China actually used in the
eight-month period totaled 27.417 billion US dollars, down 1.45
percent.
</P>
<P>
The number of overseas-funded projects for the January-August
period edged down 0.29 percent on a yearly basis to 13,056,
according to the MOFTEC.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,646 overseas-funded projects were signed in August
alone, up 2.43 percent. However, the value of contractual overseas
investment involved in the projects inched down 2.62 percent from
a year ago to 3.68 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Also in August, China actually used 3.54 billion US dollars in
overseas investment, up 0.54 percent from the same month of last
year.
</P>
<P>
Official figures also show that China had approved 317,922
overseas projects by the end of August.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
