<HEADLINE> Nanjing Massacre Photos Go on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Nearly 500 photos revealing
the truth of the Nanjing Massacre were placed on the internet
today jointly by the Jiangsu Multi-media Telecommunications
Bureau, a memorial hall for the victims and a local information
company.
</P>
<P>
The move is aimed at bringing to light the crimes of the
Japanese aggressor troops and exposing some persons' attempt to
reverse the history.
</P>
<P>
Relevant materials in Japanese and English will also be sent to
the internet in the near future. 
</P>
