<HEADLINE> Microsoft Taps Chongqing's Information Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Three documents have been
signed here today between China's Chongqing municipal government,
Chongqing Municipal Science and Technological Commission and
U.S. Microsoft.
</P>
<P>
The three documents are: a memorandum of cooperation between
the Chongqing municipal government and Microsoft (China), a letter
of intent of cooperation between the General Office of Chongqing
municipal government and Microsoft (China), and a framework
agreement on cooperative plans to train computer software talents
between Chongqing Science and Technology Commission and Microsoft
(China).
</P>
<P>
According to these documents, Microsoft will help Chongqing
introduce office automation and standardize computer softwares,
and the Chongqing municipal government pledges to further beef up
its efforts to protect intellectual property rights and create a
still more favorable environment for investment.
</P>
<P>
These documents signify the start of cooperation between
Microsoft and Chongqing Municipality in advancing this
municipality's information and software industry.  
</P>
</TEXT>
