<HEADLINE> Art Show on Late Marshal Peng Held </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A painting and calligraphy
show to mark the centenary of the birth of late marshal Peng
Dehuai is being held at the Military Museum of the Chinese
People's Revolution in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The show consists of over 280 works from the mainland, Hong
Kong and Taiwan as well as Singapore and Australia.
</P>
<P>
Peng was born on October 24, 1898. He fought courageously
against the Japanese aggressors and the Nationalist-led army in
the civil war. He was wrongly punished for his outspoken criticism
of immature economic practices in the late 1950s.
</P>
<P>
In mid-October, a memorial hall on him as well as a bronze
statute was expected to be unveiled.
</P>
<P>
A pictorial book and some other books on the late marshal's
revolutionary deeds and personality will soon to be published, as
part of the memorial activities on the 100th anniversary of his
birth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
