<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.N. Observer Forces Attacked in Angola </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Three soldiers of the United
Nations' observer forces were wounded and 10 others went missing
after they were attacked by the opposition UNITA forces in
Kwanza-Norte province in northwestern Angola.
</P>
<P>
The forces were escorting a fleet of U.N. vehicles carrying
food aid 15 km north of Lucala city on their way to Uige Province
Wednesday when fighters of the National Union for Total
Independence of Angola (UNITA) mounted on them, the Angolan News
Agency reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The three wounded U.N. soldiers were saved by Angolan national
police who rushed to their rescue, but they failed to find 10 of
the U.N. troops, a local policeman said.
</P>
<P>
He said there were no casualties of civilians, and that the
wounded men had been sent to hospital for treatment.
</P>
<P>
Nine of the 17 U.N. vehicles were destroyed, with many goods
aboard damaged. 
</P>
</TEXT>
