<HEADLINE> Jewish Settler Opens Fire at Palestinian Students </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A Jewish settler opened
fire Thursday at Palestinian students near the West Bank city of
Ramallah, killing one of them and injuring another, Jerusalem
Media and Communication Center (JMCC) reported.
</P>
<P>
The incident occurred near Ein Areek-Beitounia intersection,
south west of Ramallah, a short while ago when the students were
returning home after school.
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old Palestinian student, Iyad Rawhi Karabesh, was
killed and 16-year-old Issa Mahamoud Jabareen wounded, the JMCC
said.
</P>
<P>
On hearing the news, Palestinian villagers at Ein Areek were
angered and went out of control, clashing with Israeli soldiers
and police.
</P>
<P>
More Israeli security forces were sent to the village in order
to maintain order and the Israeli side did not give the reason
behind the shooting, but said it was under investigation.
</P>
</TEXT>
