<HEADLINE> Primakov Assures EU of Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny
Primakov on Thursday reassured the European Union that Russia
would stay on the course of reform and do everything possible to
restore investor confidence.
</P>
<P>
The talks between Primakov and a senior EU delegation focused
on Russia-EU relations from the perspective of supporting Russia's
restoration of social and economic stability and continuation of
reforms, the Interfax reported, quoting the Russian government
information board.
</P>
<P>
The EU delegation included Austrian Foreign Minister Wolfgang
Schussel, German Foreign Minister Klaus Kinkel and British Deputy
Foreign Secretary Joyce Quin, the so-called troika, and Hans van
den Broek, a member of the European Commission.
</P>
<P>
Primakov welcomed the EU officials, saying the visit itself was
a show of support for Russia.
</P>
<P>
The EU accounts for 40 percent of investments in Russia and 30
percent of Russia's overall foreign trade turnover.
</P>
<P>
Russian Deputy Prime Minister Alexander Shokhin and Foreign
Minister Igor Ivanov also were present at the talks.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, Shokhin told reporters that Russia was ready
to correct the previous government's decision of August 17 to
impose a restriction on redemption of short-term treasury bonds
held by Western banks.
</P>
<P>
He said Primakov had given him the power to make such a
statement, adding that the measure was necessary for restoration
of Western investors' confidence in Russia.
</P>
<P>
"The method Russia used in mid-August to try to solve its
financial problems does not conform to international practice,"
Shokhin said.
</P>
<P>
"However,, a return to the situation as it was before August 17
will not be on the agenda," he added.
</P>
<P>
The EU delegation also held talks with Gennady Seleznyov,
speaker of the State Duma, or lower house of parliament.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov said control of the use of foreign loans, including
by the lenders themselves, was crucial. 
</P>
</TEXT>
