Ryutaro Hashimoto said here Thursday that Tokyo will continue to
support Russian reforms without setting conditions or interfering
in Russia's domestic affairs.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto, now senior foreign affairs advisor to the current
Japanese premier, made the pledge while meeting Russian President
Boris Yeltsin, the Itar-Tass news agency reported, quoting
Japanese Embassy spokesman Akio Kawato.
</P>
<P>
Hashimoto also reiterated the intention for the two countries
to conclude a peace treaty before the year 2000.
</P>
<P>
