Hashimoto put forward a new initiative on solving the issue, and
Yeltsin had promised to give a formal reply during Japanese Prime
Minister Keizo Obuchi's scheduled visit to Moscow in November.
</P>
<P>
Kawato said the issue was not raised at the Thursday meeting
between Yeltsin and Hashimoto.
</P>
<P>
"We proceed from the point that President Yeltsin will keep his
word," Kawato said.
</P>
<P>
The two also confirmed that the recent change of governments in
the two countries will not affect bilateral cooperation, Kawato
said.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin praised Hashimoto' contributions to the improvement in
bilateral relations.  
