<HEADLINE> Palestinians Outraged After Shooting Incident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 17 (Xinhua)-- A Jewish settler opened
fire Thursday at Palestinian students near West Bank city of
Ramallah, causing outranges among the Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
The settler opened fire at a group of Palestinian students
near Ein Areek-Beitounia Intersection, south west of Rammalah, a
Palestinian self-rule area.
</P>
<P>
The 15-year-old Palestinian student Iyad Rawhi Karabesh was
killed by the fire and 16-year-old Issa Mahamoud Jabareen was
injured in the shooting.
</P>
<P>
Outraged Palestinian villagers at Ein Areek clashed with
Israeli soldiers and police in protest against the shooting.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian National Authority (PNA) criticized strongly
about the shooting and held the Israeli government fully
responsible for the incident, the Voice of Palestine (VOP) said.
</P>
