<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Security Council Calls for Peaceful Solution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In an oral statement to the press here, Hans Dahlgren,
president of the 15-member Security Council, said that the
Security Council members "have expressed the sense of urgency
caused by the deteriorating situation" in Congo (K).
</P>
<P>
The Security Council wants "to reaffirm its obligation to
respect the territorial integrity and sovereignty" of Congo (K),
and "the need for all countries in the region to refrain from any
interference in each other's internal affairs," the statement
said.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council also reaffirm the initiation of peaceful
talks with a view to achieving the national reconciliation, the
statement said.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council also voiced the need to respect human
rights, the humanitarian law and the access of the humanitarian
organizations on the field, the statement added.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council members also expressed concerns over
"the continued flow of arms to the conflict region" in the
central African country.
</P>
<P>
The statement coincided with joint international efforts to
bring an end to the conflict in Congo (K), which broke out in
early August in the eastern part of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
