<HEADLINE> Iranian Passenger Bus Flies into Euphrates River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A Iranian passenger bus has
flew into the Euphrates River in Turkey Thursday, but no
information on the casualties is available now, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the Iranian bus heading for Iran flew
into the river two kilometers after passing over the Sansa Bridge
about 56 kilometers near Erzincan, eastern Turkey.
</P>
<P>
Badly-off Iranians prefer road traffic in and out the country.
Therefore passenger buses are operating on daily basis between
Iranian capital Tehran and Turkish major cities like Ankara and
Istanbul. 
</P>
