<HEADLINE> Regional Fund Set up to Curb Drug Abuse in W. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Coordinators of drug control
panels in the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS)
have endorsed the setting up of a regional fund for financing
drug control activities, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A statement issued by the ECOWAS Secretariat in Nigerian
capital Abuja was quoted as saying that the fund would be used to
support the regional plan of action on drug control, provide
grants to national committees and assistance to inter-ministerial
drug control committees and non-governmental organizations.
</P>
<P>
The coordinators who attended a five-day meeting in Abuja also
adopted a regional drug control priority program for the period
of 1999-2002 and an action plan for the control of drugs in West
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The meeting which ended Thursday lauded Nigeria's intention to
upgrade the narcotic officers training school in the country to
international standard. 
