University, made the call when opening a two-day national
workshop on computer sciences here Thursday, Radio Uganda
reported.
</P>
<P>
With the development of information technology like Internet
and E-mail, children must be assisted to acquire the skills to
access information through computers, he said.
</P>
<P>
A UNESCO official said on this occasion that Ugandans can be
part of the globap village after acquiring computer knowledge and
decided to expand Uganda's capacity in computer literacy.
</P>
<P>
Though still one of the poorest countries in the world, Uganda
has now had a booming economy which grows at more than 5 percent
annually in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The economic development requires advanced technology imported
from outside Uganda.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, Uganda attaches great importance to
education, especially primary education, to make the young
generation more creative and productive. 
