<HEADLINE> 15,000 Pigs Die of African Swine Fever in Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Nigeria has lost about 15,000
pigs due to the current epidemic of african Swine Fever while
m~?than 12,000 pigs are afflicted with the disease, the News
Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Kesley David-West, consultant to the Food and Agricultural
Organization (FAO), was quoted as saying in Abeokuta of Ogun
state that the deadly viral disease is spreading in the country,
especially in Ogun and Lagos states.
</P>
<P>
David-West who is on an inspection visit to the country noted
that although the disease is not harmful to human being, the meat
of afflicted pigs should not be eaten.
</P>
<P>
He urged law enforcement agents to ensure that diseased pigs
and pork were not transported from one country to another so as
to curb the spread of the fever in the West African0region.
</P>
<P>
The African Swine Fever was first discovered in Lagos and Ogun
states a few weeks ago, and spreading fast to other states in
Nigeria. 
</P>
