<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank approved
Thursday two loans totaling 164.5 million U.S. dollars for two
projects in Brazil and Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
A loan of 100 million dollars is earmarked for Brazil's disease
surveillance and control project.
</P>
<P>
This project will improve and strengthen the national disease
surveillance and control system to reduce mortality and morbidity
resulting from communicable diseases.
</P>
<P>
