<HEADLINE> Portuguese Paintings Expo to Be Held In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition of Portuguese
contemporary painting works is due to open at the China Art
Gallery in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
The display of 32 paintings pieces from 18 modern Portuguese
masters, will be the No.7 of the Serial Exhibitions of '98 China
Year of International Fine Arts.
</P>
<P>
All the works come from the collection of the Center of Modern
Art of the Calouste Gulbenkian Foundation of Portugal.
</P>
<P>
Contemporary art started in Portugal early this century. Like
Ranias' geometrical cubism, Da Costa's super-realism and
Rodrigues' new way of image depiction, they all helped to form the
Portuguese contemporary arts in the course of development.
</P>
<P>
But only in recent years, Portuguese contemporary art becomes
more diversified.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the exhibition represents a major part of the
Portuguese Cultural Month, which is to be marked here in mid
October and to comprise series of displays and exhibitions
including painting works, films, photographs, books and music.
