<HEADLINE> NATO Finishes Military Exercises in Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- NATO on Thursday completed its
multi-national military exercise which started Saturday in
Macedonia, reported the Rilindja newspaper in Skopje on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The military exercise had achieved its expected targets in both
organization work and spot performance, said Colonel Markovski,
one of the commanders of the drill.
</P>
<P>
About 1500 soldiers from 13 NATO member states including the
United States and 12 countries of the Partnership for Peace
Program, including Albania, attended the exercise.
</P>
<P>
The exercise, divided into three stages, comprised 22 drill
actions including air attack, air transportation, landing from the
air and conveying humanitarian relief facilities.
</P>
<P>
It is the second time in one month that NATO has conducted
large-scale manoeuvres to show its military strength around
strife-torn Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The first one was held in Albania from August 17 to 22. 
