<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Macao Social Bodies Support Stationing Troops in Macao SAR </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of two major social
bodies in Macao said here Friday that they support the decision of
China's central government to station troops in the future Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
They made the remarks following Chinese Vice-Premier Qian
Qichen's speech in Beijing Friday morning that the central
government will send an appropriate quantity of troops to Macao
after its return to the motherland in December 1999.
</P>
<P>
Leong Heng Kao, deputy council director of the Macao Federation
of Neighborhood Communities, told reporters that it is a "correct
and necessary" decision for the central government to station
troops in the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
"The decision entirely conforms to relevant stipulation in the
Basic Law of Macao," he said, adding that the stationing of troops
will "be of far-reaching significance for Macao's social stability
and economic growth after its return."
</P>
<P>
Ho Kam Ha, another deputy council director of the federation,
said that Macao residents are not afraid of the troops, but feel a
sense of safety.
</P>
<P>
"We visited some residents today, who all support the central
government's decision and believe that the People's Liberation
Army (PLA) troops are well-disciplined," Ho said.
</P>
<P>
There were many touching scenes showing PLA officers and
soldiers braving the floods this summer to save lives and
property of the people when some parts of China were hit by
serious flooding, she said.
</P>
<P>
Ho noted that the PLA troops stationed in Hong Kong have been
in good terms with residents there over the past year.
</P>
<P>
"The central government's decision of sending troops to Macao
is for the good of Macao people," she said.
</P>
<P>
Pun Iok Lan, vice-president of the Macao Federation of Trade
Unions, also said that workers in different sectors in Macao are
delighted on hearing the decision. 
</P>
</TEXT>
