<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Refrigerator Compressor Producer in Tianjin </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A refrigerator compressor
producer financed by a Sino-Italian joint venture began operations
in Tianjin on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The manufacturer, with an annual production capacity of three
million compressor units, is considered the largest of its kind in
China.
</P>
<P>
The company, called Zanussi Electrical Equipment Tianjin
Co. Ltd, is a joint venture of the Zanussi Group and the Haihe
Refrigerator Factory of Tianjin. The joint venture was established
in 1993 at a cost of 28 million U.S. dollars, and was then capable
of producing one million refrigerators a year.
</P>
<P>
Both partners agreed to expand production scale and raise
annual refrigerator production capacity to three million units in
1996 by adding 60 million U.S. dollars of investment to import the
world's latest technologies and equipment.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the newly operational production
lines will be able to produce refrigerator compressors with
specifications ranging from 60 liters to 280 liters.
</P>
<P>
One estimate notes that China has a refrigerator market
potential exceeding 50 million units.
</P>
<P>
Zanussi Group is a member of Electrolux, the world's leading
home appliance producer which led the world in developing
freon-free refrigerators in 1992. Electrolux invested in China to
manufacture products including refrigerators and dust collectors.
</P>
</TEXT>
