<HEADLINE> First Suspect Extradited from UK to HK After Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The first suspect
extradited from the United Kingdom after the handover was returned
to Hong Kong Friday.
</P>
<P>
The suspect, a 24-year-old British man wanted in connection
with drug trafficking in 1996, was escorted back from London by
two Hong Kong police officers. He will appear in Eastern
Magistracy Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The suspect was reportedly found in possession of a quantity of
cannabis resin, ice and cocaine when stopped and searched by
police officers on Hong Kong street in January 18, 1996.
</P>
<P>
He was subsequently charged with trafficking in and possession
of dangerous drugs and granted court bail.
</P>
<P>
While waiting for hearing at the High Court, the Briton jumped
bail. He was eventually caught in England on June 25, last year.
</P>
<P>
The British authority agreed on August 19 this year to the
extradition of the suspect and formally signed the order for his
return in late August. 
</P>
