<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official said
here Friday that the stationing of troops in the future Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR) will be conducive to lasting
prosperity and stability in the territory.
</P>
<P>
Zong Guangyao, deputy director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao
Branch, made the remark when asked to comment on the decision of
China's central government to send troops to Macao after it
returns to the motherland in December 1999.
</P>
<P>
At the third plenary session of the Preparatory Committee for
the Macao SAR held in Beijing Friday morning, Chinese Vice-Premier
Qian Qichen said that the central government will station an
appropriate quantity of troops in the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
"The stationing of troops in the Macao SAR symbolizes China's
resumption of exercising sovereignty over Macao," Zong Guangyao
said.
</P>
<P>
"I believe that people of various sectors in Macao will welcome
and support the central government's decision of stationing
troops," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to the 14th article of the Basic Law of Macao, the
central government is responsible for managing defense affairs in
the Macao SAR. 
