<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0102 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Invasion Day of Northeast China Remembered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- For four years running,
northeast China's Shenyang city sounded air-raid alarms for three
minutes starting at 22:20 on September 18, to remind residents of
the day of the Japanese army's invasion in 1931.
</P>
<P>
This year, the city did more to mark that shameful day by
holding a ceremony to hoist the national flag at the square before
the provincial government building at 8:00 this morning, with some
3,000 former soldiers, officers and ordinary citizens gathering
solemnly below the flag.
</P>
<P>
Also this morning, over 2,000 schools held the national flag
hoisting ceremony on campuses. Some students also made speeches
under the flag, calling on fellow students to study hard for the
grand goal of building a strong China.
</P>
<P>
"September 18 is a day of humiliation for the Chinese people,"
said Gu Tiantian, a student from the Shenyang No. 2 Middle
School. "Always remembering the national humiliation and
invigorating China is youngsters' unshirkable responsibility."
</P>
<P>
Exactly on this evening 67 years ago, the Japanese army
stationed in northeast China suddenly launched attacks against the
Nationalist government's army in Shenyang, under an excuse. With
Chiang Kai-shek preoccupied with wiping out the "communist
bandits," the whole northeast China were lost to the Japanese
within just about four months. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
