<HEADLINE> China's Market Survey Sector Grows Rapidly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- China now has more than 800
market survey agencies and over half of them are based in Beijing,
Shanghai and Guangzhou, according to official sources at a meeting
today ended here today.
</P>
<P>
Of the total, more than 700 are run by individuals, private
firms or units other than government-managed agencies.
</P>
<P>
Over the recent years, China's market surveying sector has been
growing at an annual rate of more than 100 percent. The business
volume last year was 500 million yuan, with the figure for this
year expected to reach 600-to-800 million yuan, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
They noted, however, that the industry's credibility has been
affected by some non-standard practices cropping up in the process
of rapid expansion.
</P>
<P>
So it has become imperative to strengthen self-discipline
within the sector, the source said.
</P>
<P>
The three-day meeting was attended by representatives from more
than 200 surveying agencies and is the largest of its kind.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
