<HEADLINE> China, Germany to Jointly Build Forest by Tongting Lake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- China and Germany plan to
build 31,000 hectares of forests around China's second largest
Tongting Lake in five years to offer an ecological screen for
agricultural production by the lake.
</P>
<P>
At the second work meeting on the ecological forest program
that closed today in Changsha, capital of central Hunan Province,
both sides pledged to make a total investment worth 94.33 million
yuan (about 11.4 million U.S. dollars), 63.6 percent of which will
be gratis investment from Germany.
</P>
<P>
They agreed that the program will help improve local ecological
conditions at the middle reaches of the Yangtze and Tongting Lake,
offer ecological shelter for farm production and water conservancy
project construction, and prevent flooding.
</P>
<P>
Since preparations for the program began in December last year,
China and Germany have built 560 hectares of exemplary forests
along the lake. Both sides are expected to build 3,000 hectares of
forests this year, and the Hunan provincial government has
appropriate 1.8 million yuan to this end.  
</P>
</TEXT>
