<HEADLINE> 65 Percent Employed in EU Service Sector </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The service sector accounts
for 65 percent of total employment in the 15-nation European Union
(EU), EU statistics showed Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Luxembourg-based statistical office of the European
community (Eurostat) said the service sector, which is described
as the "hub of employment creation and workplace flexibility
within Europe", employs 97 million people, mostly in the retail
trade.
</P>
<P>
Eurostat also said 80 percent of working women are found in the
service sector.
</P>
<P>
Four EU member states which posted more than 70 percent in
service sector employment are Luxembourg (74.1 percent), the
Netherlands (73.1 percent), Sweden (70.9 percent) and Britain
(70.6 percent).
</P>
<P>
Service sector employment takes up 56.5 percent and 56.8
percent of total employment in Portugal and Greece respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
