<HEADLINE> Ningxia University Marks 40th Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YINCHUAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Ningxia University, in this
capital of northwest China's Ningxia Hui Autonomous Region,
celebrated its 40th anniversary today.
</P>
<P>
The University, the first of its kind in the mostly moslem
region, has a faculty of more than 2,000, and more than 10,000
students; and it has eight disciplines, 40 majors, eight doctoral
programs, and 34 research institutes, according to university
president Zhang Kui.
</P>
<P>
"Graduates of our university have become an important force for
the economic and social progress of our region," Zhang said at a
celebration ceremony.
</P>
<P>
About two thirds of all high-level officials at the regional
government and officials at or above the county level in Ningxia
graduated from Ningxia University, according to official data.
</P>
<P>
To date, Ningxia University has set up cooperative ties with
higher education institutions and research institutes in more than
20 countries, including the United States, Canada, Germany, Japan,
Britain, Australia, Turkey, Russia and Kazakhstan.
</P>
<P>
Ningxia University is one of China's 200 higher education
institutions allowed to accept overseas students. So far it has
trained master-level students for the United States, Japan, Iran,
Kuwait and the Republic of Korea (ROK).  
</P>
