<HEADLINE> Sino-US Venture to Develop Bohai Sea Oil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The China National Offshore
Oil Corp (CNOOC) and US-based Texaco and ARCO inked a contract
today to develop China's third largest offshore oilfield --
Qinhuangdao (QHD) 32-6 -- in Bohai Bay.
</P>
<P>
CNOOC discovered the field in 1995. The QHD field which covers
a 250-square-kilometer area at depths of 20 meters is located 20
kilometers offshore in Bohai Bay. The field has proven reserves of
170 million tons.
</P>
<P>
The companies expect to complete a formal development plan by
the end of this year. Plans call for the field to enter production
in the year 2001 and annual production is expected to hit 3.4
million tons.
</P>
<P>
CNOOC will operate and retain a 51 percent share in the
venture. Texaco and ARCO will each hold 24.5 percent shares in the
operation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
