<HEADLINE> Cyprus Stock Market Maintains Flat Course </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Cyprus Stock Market
maintained its flat course for the second consecutive week, while
volume of transactions was sustained at satisfactory levels, a
weekly market review said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The review, issued by Cyprus Investment and Securities
Corporation Limited (CISCO), said CISCO All-Share Index closed
Thursday at 439.6 points, marking a small weekly decline of 2.6
points or 0.6 percent.
</P>
<P>
The review said that most part of the weekly decline was
suffered on Monday when the market closed at 440.3 points. During
the following two days the 440 point level was repeatedly tested
and was finally broken downward on Thursday, for the first time
since August 21.
</P>
<P>
According to the review, the banking sector continues
absorbing the bulk of transactions and concentrated 46.6 percent
of the total weekly volume. Tourist stocks also appeared very
active during the past week concentrating 16.2 percent, followed
by warrants, investment companies and the manufacturing sector.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of transactions for this week was 6.3
million Cyprus pounds (about 12.6 million U.S. dollars) compared
to 6.2 million pounds (about 12.4 million dollars) the week
before, the review said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
