<HEADLINE> Shanghai Accelerates Industrial Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai, China's leading
financial and economic center, is engaged in extensive efforts to
explore new aspects of economic growth in order to offset the
impact of a number of unfavorable factors, including the financial
crisis in Asia and devastating summer flooding.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai reported an industrial output value of 378 billion
yuan for the first eight months of the year, up nine percent on
the 1997 period and two percentage points lower than targeted
figure for the year.
</P>
<P>
The city expects to achieve its goals by focusing on the
development of marketable products. Some 30 new products,
including computers, digital video disc players and auto air
conditioners for Santana and Buick models are currently in
production..
</P>
<P>
Earlier this year. a number of cosmetics producers which
previously concentrated on urban consumers have introduced
marketing programs to the potential of the rural market. The new
approach has enabled the sector to reverse losses and the sector's
sales volume jumped by 24 percent in the first seven months of the
year.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises in the electronics, machine-building, metallurgy,
chemical and building materials sectors have exhibited their
superiority in terms of equipment and services and have won bids
for a number of projects.
</P>
<P>
The foreign trade sector has adjusted its export strategies and
opened new markets. As a result, exports to the United States,
Europe and Oceania have continued to rise while exports to Asian
nations have steadily declined. 
</P>
</TEXT>
