<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 12:17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Massive Rally in Tehran to Mourn for Slain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Hundreds of thousands of
Tehranis marched along avenues and streets leading to Tehran
University Friday for a rally to condemn Afghan Taliban militia's
killing of Iranian diplomats and a reporter.
</P>
<P>
"Death with Taliban," demonstrators shouted, "No compromise, no
fear, we want to Fight."
</P>
<P>
A number of marchers carrying loaded rifles told Xinhua
correspondent that they are ready to carry out the order of the
paramount leader and Commander-in-Chief of the armed forces
Ayatollah Ali Khamenei to take revenge on the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
In tears, an old woman, Zahra Mohammad Khanlu cried out "No one
in the world kill a reporter who should have freedom to make
reports, why the Taliban killed our correspondent?"
</P>
<P>
"The Taliban who committed crimes under the name of Islam are
in fact dogs which do not recognize their masters," she said,
noting "Iran has hosted several million Afghan refugees."
</P>
<P>
Eleven Iranian diplomats and the reporter had been reported
abducted by the Taliban at the militia's seizure of Mazari Sharif,
a town in northern Afghanistan on August 8. Nine diplomats and the
reporter were confirmed dead.
</P>
<P>
The Taliban on Monday delivered to Iran the bodies of six
diplomats and the reporter of the official news agency IRNA. But
the fate of two more Iranian diplomats reported missing was still
unknown.
</P>
<P>
An Afghan refugee, Ali Abass Hohammadeh said the Afghan
refugees living in Iran are ready to return to Afghanistan to
fight against the Taliban.
</P>
<P>
At end of the rally, a resolution was read aloud inside Tehran
University where the Friday prayers congregation was held.
</P>
<P>
The resolution called for immediate release of other Iranian
nationals held captive by the Taliban and clarification of the
fate of other Iranian diplomats reported missing in northern
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The resolution urged the Iranian government to arm the Afghan
refugees living in Iran to fight the Taliban in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The resolution also warned the supporters of the Taliban,
particularly Pakistan, to stop support for the Afghan
fundamentalist group.
</P>
<P>
After the Friday prayers congregation, the mass held a funeral
procession for the six Iranian diplomats and the IRNA reporter
with the participation of senior Iranian officials, including
Majlis Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq Nouri, Foreign Minister Kamal
Kharrazi and IRGC commander Yahya Rahim Safavi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
