<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks fell
130.61 points, or 1.72 percent, Friday from the previous close to
finish the week's trade at 7,445.96.
</P>
<P>
Market turnover amounted to 4.393 billion HK dollars (563
million U.S. dollars), 489 million HK dollars (63 million U.S.
dollars) less than that of Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The key Hang Seng Index (HSI) dropped 125.75 points, or 1.66
percent, to open at 7,450.82 Friday morning.
</P>
<P>
It lost 215.86 points, or 2.85 percent, to finish Friday's
morning session at 7,360.71.
</P>
<P>
The HSI fell 284.11 points, or 3.61 percent, to close at
7,576.57 Thursday. 
</P>
