<HEADLINE> Yang Shangkun's Remains Set for Cremation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The remains of Yang Shangkun,
former Chinese President and great proletarian revolutionary,
statesman and military strategist, will be cremated on Monday in
Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Tiananmen Square, Xinhuamen Gate, the Great Hall of the People
and the Foreign Ministry in Beijing will fly national flags at
half mast to mourn the loss of the great leader.
</P>
<P>
Flags will also be lowered at the sites of Party committees and
government headquarters in all provinces, autonomous region and
municipalities, and the office of the government of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR), as well as at border ports of
entry, and land and sea ports, the Macao Branch of Xinhua News
Agency and Chinese embassies and consulates in other countries.
</P>
</TEXT>
