<HEADLINE> British Woman Shot by Gunmen in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A British woman shot by
unidentified gunmen in Kampala Thursday night is still in
critical condition in a hospital here, police sources told Xinhua
Friday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
In a telephone interview, Joel Ayiko, a police public
relations officer, said that the British national named Lucy
Carpenta was shot at ~0 p.m. Thursday at the Kisugu, Kawalye
and Kagua road junction in the capital city.
</P>
<P>
She was driving a red Isuzu Trooper when targeted by the
unknown gunmen. The bullet-riddled vehicle came to a halt in a
nearby bush from where Lucy was rescued, said a press release
issued here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Lucy was taken to Nsambya hospital and later transformed to
Mulago hospital, the release added.
</P>
<P>
Police still did not know whether she was a tourist or one
working for some organization in Uganda, how many gunmen there
were and where she was going at the time of the shooting.
</P>
<P>
The gunmen are still at large as the police are investigating
the case. 
</P>
</TEXT>
