<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran: Taliban Militia Are War Criminals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Majlis Speaker Ali
Akbar Nateq Nouri on Friday called on the international
communities to treat the Afghan Taliban militia as war criminals.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters in front of Tehran University before a
massive funeral procession for the killed Iranian diplomats and
reporter, Nouri said the international communities should show a
practical reaction to such crimes and do more than merely issuing
statements or resolutions.
</P>
<P>
On the forthcoming maneuver of the Iranian army on the
country's eastern border, Nouri termed it as a message to show
that Iran is able to defend its borders and poses no threats to
its neighboring states.
</P>
<P>
He said that the maneuver showcases Iran's national will and
determination as well as the armed forces' readiness to thwart
any possible aggression.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian army has started to transfer military forces from
various provinces to the eastern border to hold a grand war game
later this month amid spiraling tensions between Iran and the
Taliban following the Muslim group's killing of nine Iranian
diplomats and a reporter in northern Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
The massive turnout of the people in the nationwide rallies on
Friday shows their all-out support for the statement of the
supreme leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, Nouri added.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei, the Commander-in-Chief of the armed forces, on
Tuesday ordered the armed forces to be on alert to follow the
development in Afghanistan and maintain full readiness to carry
out whatever decision the country's statesmen would make. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
