<HEADLINE> 27 Power Projects Underway in Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-seven power
projects are under construction in Ethiopia to raise the country's
electric power generating capacity.
</P>
<P>
The Herald newspaper Friday quoted Sendeku Araya, official
from the Ethiopian Electric Power Corporation, as saying that the
construction of these projects began two years ago with an outlay
of 170 million U.S. Dollars obtained in aid and loan from the
Ethiopian government as well as foreign governments and
organizations.
</P>
<P>
After completion of construction, the projects will raise the
present nation-wide power supply of 371.6 megawatt to 675.6 megawatt,
said Sendeku.
</P>
<P>
Sendeku explained that the projects include the construction
works in the Gilgel Gibe hydroelectric project, the Fincha fourth
unit construction project and the strengthening of some other
power stations.
</P>
<P>
He added that the construction works in Tekeze, Gojeb and Tis
Abbay hydro-power generating projects are well being underway.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian Electric Power Corporation has plans to
construct 12 new hydro-power stations and strengthening of five
ongoing hydro-power stations in the coming five years at a cost
of 1.5 billion U.S. Dollars.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
