<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Share Prices Nose-Dive on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Share prices nose-dived on
the Singapore Stock Market Friday as the overnight plunge on Wall
Street and pre-weekend profit-taking dampened market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) dropped 28.68 point to
end at 912.74 points with the total turnover falling to 128.74
million units worth 212.72 million Singapore dollars (about 123.86
million U.S. dollars). There were 170 losers against 33 gainers
with 220 counters unchanged.
</P>
<P>
OUB F was the most active stock of the day as it registered a
volume of 9.20 million stocks traded. It was followed by KepCorp
that had 7.49 million units done. TAC 200 was next with 6.90
million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
CMSPort was the top gainer of the day as it gained 40 cents to
close at 1.60 Hong Kong dollars. Venture moved up 25 cents to
finish at 5.25 Singapore dollars. OUS edged up 24 cents to end at
1.14 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, SIA F was the biggest loser of the day as it
lost 75 cents to close at 8.10 Singapore dollars. Elec &AMP; E slid 44
cents to finish at 4.50 U.S. dollars. SIA shed off 40 cents to end
at 5.40 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said market sentiment was also weakened by spreading
rumors of an impending cut in the contribution to the Central
Provident Fund (CPF).
</P>
<P>
The local bourse was awash with rumors that the Singapore
government would announce a CPF cut by up to 15 percentage points,
traders said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
