<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0830 GMT September 18 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES -- Nike Inc., the world largest sport
footware-maker, reported Thursday its earnings fell 35 percent in
the latest quarter, which ended August 31.
</P>
<P>
The profits for the latest quarter were 163.8 million
U.S. dollasr compared to 253.1 million U.S. dollars, the sports
marketing giant said, adding that revenue fell 9 percent to 2.5
billion U.S. dollars from 2.8 billion
U.S. dollars. (Nike-Earnings-Fall)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Deputy Speaker of the State Duma Vladimir Ryzhkov has
rejected the post of deputy prime minister in charge of social
issues, the Itar-Tass news agency reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Gennady Seleznyov, speaker of the Duma,
or lower house of parliament, at the beginning of a plenary
session Friday, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin appointed Ryzhkov deputy premier on
Wednesday. (Russia-Cabinet-Ryzhkov)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HANOI -- Agriculture and forestry ministers of the Association
of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) started a two-day meeting in
Hanoi on Thursday, local press reported.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to make the region the world's leading food
producer as well as to promote the sustainable development of
forestry resources, participants of the 20th ASEAN Ministers of
Agriculture and Forestry Meeting (AMAF 20) will review and adopt
cooperation plans for food, agriculture and
forestry. (ASEAN-Meeting-Agriculture-Forestry)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
