Venezuelan President Rafael Caldera said that women have made
great contributions to the struggle for their equal rights with
men. (Meeting-Women's Rights)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- The Southeast Asian financial crisis will not lead
Italian auto company Fiat to change its plans to penetrate global
markets, Fiat top executive said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the world launch of the Alfa Romeo's new luxury
saloon, the 166, Fiat Auto Managing Director Roberto Testore said
the Italian car maker's global reach had been proven by the 166's
predecessor, the 156, which was sold in 57 countries.
</P>
<P>
He said that this figure would be outstripped by the new model,
which is expected to be sold in 60 countries starting in late
October. (Italy-Fiat)
</P>
