<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Nike Earnings Fall 35 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Nike Inc., the world
largest sport footware-maker, reported Thursday its earnings fell
35 percent in the latest quarter, which ended August 31.
</P>
<P>
The profits for the latest quarter were 163.8 million U.S. dollasr
compared to 253.1 million U.S. dollars, the sports marketing giant
said, adding that revenue fell 9 percent to 2.5 billion U.S. dollars
from 2.8 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Nike also reported orders declined 15 percent to 3.2 billion U.S.
dollars for the latest quarter, compared to the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Asian orders were down the most, 56 percent, while domestic orders
were down 7 percent and European orders decline by just 1 percent, the
company said.
</P>
<P>
Although the earnings of the latest quarter were lower than the
same period last year, it was a significant improvement from the
previous quarter, when Nike reported a 67.7 million U.S. dollars loss.
</P>
<P>
Nike blamed the drop of earnings in the latest quarter for the
continued weak sales, especially in Asia.  
</P>
</TEXT>
