<HEADLINE> Israel Seals Palestinian Territories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Israel Defense Force (IDF)
has placed a blanket closure on the Palestinian territories since
Friday morning to prevent possible terrorist attacks as the Jewish
new year falls, the army said.
</P>
<P>
The IDF closure on the territories will be in force until next
Wednesday and during this period, no Palestinian workers will be
allowed to go to work in Israel, with the exception of hospital
workers, journalists and those travelling for humanitarian
reasons, the Army Radio said.
</P>
<P>
Tension, already running high since Israeli forces killed two
Palestinian Islamic Resistance Movement (Hamas) members near
Hebron last week, increased Thursday after a Jewish settler
killed a Palestinian student and wounded another near the West
Bank city of Ramallah when he opened fire into a group of
Palestinian students.
</P>
<P>
The 35-year-old settler reported the incident to police
Thursday evening after it had been reported in the media, saying
his car had been stoned by a group of Palestinian high school
students.
</P>
<P>
The IDF will continue to remain on high alert throughout the
new year holiday which begins Sunday, bracing for revenge attacks
as threatened by Hamas for the killing of its two members. 
</P>
</TEXT>
