<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Makerere University Tightens Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Makerere University, the
most famous higher learning institution in Uganda, will beef up
security after the latest spate of bomb scares that have rocked
the capital city.
</P>
<P>
This security plan was announced by the Deputy Vice-Chancellor
Opio Epelu at a security sensitization seminar Thursday, the
Monitor daily reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
Those who live on the campus will have to be inconvenienced as
they will continuously have their luggage and cars checked at the
main entrance, said Epelu.
</P>
<P>
All the university staff who own cars will get car stickers
before the end of the year for proper identification, he added.
</P>
<P>
Even these measures cannot guarantee the security of the
university which is surrounded by slums and has no perimeter
fence.
</P>
<P>
The university administration is budgeting for a six-kilometer
fence to be installed around the campus and they have also
decided to establish checking points at the entry of each
building. And all staff members will be issued with
identification tags.
</P>
<P>
Students of the fenceless university are often reported to be
robbed, raped or scared by hooligans who reside in the slums and
attack from bushes surrounding the campus.
</P>
<P>
The university, which has admitted some 8,000 privately-funded
students this academic year, has so few dormitories that most of
the students have to rent rooms outside the campus.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that many other institutions have also stepped
up security measures.
</P>
<P>
The fresh bomb scares following the bombings in Nairobi, Kenya
and Dar es Salaam, Tanzania, have forced some embassies and
United Nations agencies here to close down.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
