<BODY>
<HEADLINE> EDS - Adds more details, background </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Ryzhkov Rejects Post of Deputy Premier
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Speaker of the State
Duma Vladimir Ryzhkov has rejected the post of deputy prime
minister in charge of social issues, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Gennady Seleznyov, speaker of the Duma,
or lower house of parliament, at the beginning of a plenary
session Friday, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin appointed Ryzhkov deputy premier on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov quoted Ryzhkov as describing the appointment as "an
arranged marriage."
</P>
<P>
"Vladimir Ryzhkov will later explain everything himself,"
Seleznyov said.
</P>
<P>
The news of his appointment reached Ryzhkov, who is also a
prominent member of the Our Home Is Russia (NDR) parliamentary
group, while he was in Strasbourg, France.
</P>
<P>
Upon returning to Moscow from Strasbourg on Thursday, Ryzhkov
told reporters that he was willing to work in the government but
had some misgivings.
</P>
<P>
"My conviction as a human being and a citizen is that whoever
can do something useful for Russia and its people must do so. For
this reason I am prepared to work in the government. I am not
shirking this responsibility or this work," the Interfax news
agency quoted him as saying.
</P>
<P>
"However, I am not quite sure that this is the position where
I can be most useful," Ryzhkov said.
</P>
<P>
Ryzhkov, born in 1966, graduated from Altai State University
and taught there after graduation. He joined the NDR in 1995, and
was elected State Duma first deputy chairman representing the NDR
in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
