<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Slight Increase of Foreign Capital Use in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- China used 3.54 billion
U.S. dollars of direct foreign funds in August, up 0.54 percent
over the same month last year, according to statistics just
released by China's Ministry of Foreign Trade and Economic
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The amount of contractual direct foreign investment stood at
3.7 billion U.S. dollars for the month, down 2.6 percent from last
year. Approved projects involving foreign funding numbered 1,646,
an increase of 2.4 percent over August last year.
</P>
<P>
From January to August, the amount of contractual direct
foreign capital and the volume actually in use reached 31.7
billion U.S. dollars and 27.4 billion U.S. dollars, up 6 percent
and down 1.5 percent respectively over the corresponding 1997
period. The total number of enterprises with overseas fundings
approved stood at 13,056, down 0.29 percent compared with last
year's corresponding figure.
</P>
<P>
By the end of August, China has used a total of 249.3 billion
U.S. dollars of direct foreign capital, recorded a contractual
direct foreign investment of 552.9 billion U.S. dollars, and
approved 317,922 projects involving foreign funding.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
