<HEADLINE> China Can Win 20 Golds at Asian Games, Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- China can achieve its goal
of winning 20 gold medals from track and field in the upcoming
13th Bangkok Asian Games without coach Ma Junren's runners, a top
official said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Shang Xiutang, secretary general of the Chinese Athletics
Association (CAA), said that the absence of "Ma's Family Army"
will not affect China's status as Asia's leader in track and
field.
</P>
<P>
"We're confident to win 20 gold medals at the Asian Games in
December," Shang said.
</P>
<P>
Chinese athletes, who usually bury their heads in training and
adjustment after a whole year's competition in December, are
working hard to adapt themselves to Bangkok's hot conditions.
</P>
<P>
China won 22 out of 43 gold medals from track and field in the
12th Asian Games at Hiroshima, Japan, in 1994. World women's
3,000 meters record holder Qu Yunxia, a member of "Ma's Family
Army", stroke a golden double in the 800 and 1,500 meters.
</P>
<P>
The middle-and long-distance runners of "Ma's Family Army"
have been disqualified from taking part in the Asian Games as the
unorthodox coach Ma Junren failed to participate in any of this
season's national Grand Prix events as required.
</P>
<P>
"We will not change the rules to let Ma's team go," Shang
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
