<HEADLINE> Russia's Ryzhkov Rejects Post of Deputy Premier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
MOSCOW, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Deputy Speaker of the State
Duma Vladimir Ryzhkov has rejected the post of deputy prime
minister in charge of social issues, the Itar-Tass news agency
reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
This was announced by Gennady Seleznyov, speaker of the Duma,
or lower house of parliament, at the beginning of a plenary
session Friday, Tass said.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin appointed Ryzhkov deputy premier on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Seleznyov quoted Ryzhkov as describing the appointment as "an
arranged marriage." 
</P>
