<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Another Kenyan Bank Placed Under Statutory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The Trust Bank Ltd., ranked
six in Kenya's banking industry, has been placed under statutory
management of the central bank Thursday after it failed to honor
360 million Shillings (6.05 million U.S. Dollars) in checks.
</P>
<P>
This followed a run on the bank by depositors after a company
filed Thursday a lawsuit claiming the bank was facing insolvency
and should be put into receivership, local press reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The Central Bank of Kenya (CBK) moved quickly to avert the
crisis, appointing Michael Muhindi, a former senior manager with
Standard Chartered, to run the bank.
</P>
<P>
CBK Governor Micah Cheserem also confirmed Thursday that
another bank, Bullion Bank, had reported that it was facing
similar difficulties.
</P>
<P>
Cheserem appealed to the depositors - mainly Asians - not to
make panic withdrawals that could cause a ripple effect in the
banking sector.
</P>
<P>
"If the depositors remain calm, we can save the Trust Bank. It
has many assets and we would like to save it," he said.
</P>
<P>
The governor said that the Trust Bank, plus all its branches,
will remain closed Friday until the new management takes over.
</P>
<P>
"This arrangement will allow the bank time to improve on its
liquidity through the sale of its properties as well as injection
of additional capital and/or loan recoveries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Trust Bank locked out customers in all its branches at 2:00
p.m. Thursday as the directors went into an urgent meeting on the
crisis.
</P>
<P>
At the Bullion Bank, customers also turned away after being
told the bank was trying to sort out something with the Central
Bank.
</P>
<P>
Trust Bank deposits by August 31 stood at 9.3 billion
Shillings (156.3 million U.S. Dollars) with 17 branches and 622
employees across the country.
</P>
<P>
Cheserem said the new statutory manager will sell off several
of the bank's properties which should facilitate the re-opening
of the bank "at the earliest opportunity."
</P>
<P>
Last week, the Reliance Bank was also put under statutory
management after it failed to pay 160 million Shillings in
overnight borrowing. Four of its directors and managers have
been charged for fraud.
</P>
<P>
There are 55 banks and financial institutions in the east
African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
