<HEADLINE> New Zealand Stocks Finish Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The New Zealand
sharemarket
closed lower here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The NZSE40 Index ended 27 points lower at 1,735 with a turnover
of
76 million NZ dollars (38.6 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Air New Zealand and Brierley Investments continued to be stable

at 162 cents and 49 cents. Fletcher Energy lost 15 cents to 320
cents
and AMP 5 cents to 2,425 cents. Telecom and Carter Holt Harvey
fell
12 cents each to 738 cents and 132 cents respectively. Fletcher
Paper
and Fletcher Forest dropped 4 cents each to 103 cents and 56 cents

respectively. Auckland Airport dipped 1 cent to 185 cents while
Fletcher Building gained 3 cents to 204 cents. 
