<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Liaoning Improves Marine Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province has improved its marine environment by improving urban
wastewater disposal and controlling sources of industrial
pollution.
</P>
<P>
With a coastline stretching 2,920 km and marine area of 68,000
square kilometers, the province has improved more than 1,000
polluting enterprises, relocated an additional 200 ventures and
closed hundreds of heavily polluting operations.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning invested 2.3 billion yuan (277 million U.S. dollars)
to construct facilities for treating industrial and domestic
wastewater generated in coastal cities.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning has also established a special fund to support
pollution control along the Liaohe River, the longest in the
province which flows through a number of industrial cities. The
goal of the fund is to substantially reduce the volume of
wastewater flowing into the sea.
</P>
<P>
The province has also established eight maritime nature
reserves covering 1.12 million sq.km. as part the effort to
strengthen the protection of maritime resources. 
</P>
