<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Railway Departments Support Floods Relief Effort </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 18 (Xinhua) -- China's railway departments
have gone all the way to support this summer's flood relief
efforts by transporting over 2.5 tons of material and equipment in
45,000 freight cars.
</P>
<P>
The departments also provided transportation for over 117,000
soldiers engaged in the effort and extended every possible effort
to guarantee the smooth operation of transportation arteries,
according to the Ministry of Railways.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has pledged to provide convenient transport
in coming days to enable people engaged in the effort to return to
their homes and jobs.
</P>
<P>
The railway system handled 2.63 million passengers daily during
August, down 1.4 percent on the 1997 period. The system also
handled 68,400 freight cars during the period, down 6,600 units on
the targeted figure.
</P>
<P>
The passenger volume for the July-August period stood at 163
million due to the large number of college students returning home
for the summer vacation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
