<HEADLINE> World Champion Skater Michelle Kwan Graduates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- World figure skating
champion Michelle Kwan officially graduated from her high school
on Thursday, receiving her diploma from principal in a private
ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Kwan, 18, earned a near-perfect 3.9 out of 4.0 grade-p
oint-average in her senior year, and graduated with a cumulative
GPA (grades 9-12) of 3.61.
</P>
<P>
"I had two major goals this year -- to make it to the Olympics
and to graduate high school," said Kwan, who claimed five titles
and an Olympic silver medal this past skating season.
"Accomplishing both has really made it a dream year."
</P>
<P>
Kwan will take a year off from full-time studies to
concentrate on her skating. She plans to enter a college in the
fall of 1999.
</P>
<P>
"It has been a pleasure to watch Michelle mature and develop
as a student ans as a person," said Linda Ward, the supervising
teacher for Kwan's independent study program. "Her ability to
successfully combine and balance athletics and academics in her
life is a remarkable achievement. She is truly a role model for
all student-athletes."  
</P>
</TEXT>
