<HEADLINE>   ASEAN Agriculture, Forestry Ministers Meet in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Agriculture and forestry
ministers of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN)
started a two-day meeting in Hanoi on Thursday, local press
reported.
</P>
<P>
In an effort to make the region the world's leading food
producer as well as to promote the sustainable development of
forestry resources, participants of the 20th ASEAN Ministers of
Agriculture and Forestry Meeting (AMAF 20) will review and adopt
cooperation plans for food, agriculture and forestry.
</P>
<P>
A revised memorandum of understanding on ASEAN cooperation and
agro-forestry trade promotion program will be signed during the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam News Agency quoted Vietnamese Minister of Agriculture
and Rural Development Le Huy Ngo as saying that Vietnam will
present assessment of impacts of the current economic crisis on
agriculture, forestry and fishery in the region as well as
measures to ease negative impacts.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Vietnam will propose the establishment of a special
force to preserve forests in the region, Ngo said.
</P>
<P>
Ngo will be elected AMAF 20 chairman for the 1998-99 term.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN Deputy General Secretary Suthad Setboosarng attended the
meeting.
</P>
<P>
A delegation of cambodia's agriculture, forestry and fishery
ministry also participated in the meeting as observers. 
</P>
