<HEADLINE> Anti-Smuggling Efforts Successful in Guangdong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Customs officials in
Guangdong Province in south China crashed 920 smuggling cases
involving 630 million yuan (about 78.7 million U.S. dollars)
between July and August.
</P>
<P>
Provincial sources attribute these achievements to
increased customs efforts on all fronts since July this year.
</P>
<P>
Among the confiscated goods, there was a decrease in the amount
of commodities lately targeted by smugglers such as oil products
and edible oil, which indicates the anti-smuggling efforts are
going in the right direction, sources said.
</P>
<P>
In August, customs seized 9,336 tons of oil products and
316 tons of edible oil, down 66.5 percent and 32.8 percent over
the previous month.  
</P>
