arrested Randy Spradling, alias "Jeffrey Paterson," one of the
most wanted drug traffickers in the United States.
</P>
<P>
Spradling was arrested in the west Mexican city of Guadalajara,
official reports from the Attorney General's Office (PGR) said,
and he would soon be extradited.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. trafficker is wanted by the Federal Bureau of
Investigation for his involvement in two tons of smuggled cocaine
seized by police in California.
</P>
<P>
The PGR said that Spradling, who pretended to be a Canadian
national, financed and organized a system to smuggle several tons
of cocaine into the U.S.
</P>
<P>
The PGR said Spradling was jailed in 1992 in the Puente Grande
Prison in Jalisco and was released in 1994. 
