<HEADLINE> Floods Affect 11,000 Industrial Units in Bangladesh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- About 11,000 industrial units
have been badly affected by the severe floods that gripped
Bangladesh for over two months, and the losses to the sector will
exceed 20 billion taka (425.5 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed by Bangladesh Chamber of Industry (BCI)
President Sharif Afzal Hossain while apprising the representatives
of donor countries and agencies of the flood damage to the
industrial sector at a meeting here Thursday, The Bangladesh
Observer daily reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The loss to the garment sector would be more than six billion
taka (127.7 million dollars), small and cottage industries over
5.7 billion taka (121.3 million dollars), and other industrial
units would incur a loss of about eight billion taka (170.2
million dollars), according to a preliminary assessment of the
damage by the deluge, he told the meeting.
</P>
<P>
The BCI chief urged the donors to provide soft-term loans to
the private sector for the post-flood rehabilitation programs,
particularly in the infrastructure and industrial sectors.
</P>
<P>
The representatives of the World Bank and the Asian Development
Bank replied that the donor agencies would assess the extent of
flood damage and consult with the government to provide assistance
to the private sector industrial units. 
</P>
</TEXT>
