<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0241 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Experts Expect Reverse of Bulgaria's Tumbling Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Despite plunge in Bulgaria's
stock prices and trade volume on Thursday under influence of the
Russian economic crisis, experts foresee a market reverse soon.
</P>
<P>
Stock prices may see a reverse tendency and may even double
within a month or two, said experts of the Bulgarian Association
of Licensed Investment Intermediaries.
</P>
<P>
Foreign investors are not expected to show interest in
Bulgaria in the following month, but a possible additional release
of securities may attract their attention. A new issue would also
boost trade, but this effect cannot be achieved by Bulgarian
investors alone, the experts believed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the Board of Directors of the Bulgarian Stock
Exchange (BSE) is expected to adopt Association-drafted rules of
procedure of a new market, which will not require the presence of
the brokers on the Exchange, according to Kamen Kolchev, chairman
of the governing board of the association.
</P>
<P>
The rules, to be included in the BSE articles, have already
received unofficial approval from BSE leadership. A second stage
of the project involves building up information channels between
the BSE and each of the investment intermediaries.
</P>
<P>
The new market would not differ from the currently operating
free market from the point of view of the clients, said Kolchev.
</P>
<P>
One of the rules involves introducing a 10 per cent barrier
for the daily fluctuation of prices. Currently this barrier equals
5 percent on the official market while on the free market trading
is unrestricted.
</P>
<P>
The association also insists on abandoning the practice of
frustrating deals. Under the law, the stock exchange is
irreversible; it is the brokers who carry the responsibility for a
wrongly struck deal, said Kamen Kolchev. In his view, a frustrated
deal is used to manipulate the market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
