<HEADLINE> US First Lady to Open International Women's Forum in Sofia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- United States First Lady
Hillary Clinton will open an international women's conference on
October 10-11 in Sofia, an official report said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
According to the wife of Bulgarian President Peter Stoyanov,
Antonina Stoyanova, Mrs Clinton will be a special guest at the
conference on "Women in the 21st Century: Overcoming the Hurdles
to Sustainable Development in Southeastern Europe" during her
visit here.
</P>
<P>
The conference is a joint project of Mrs Stoyanova, the wife of
Bulgarian Prime Minister Ivan Kostov, and the wife of National
Assembly Chairman Yordan Sokolov. The three women held a news
conference Thursday to promote the aims of the forum and announce
the participants.
</P>
<P>
Mrs Stoyanova said the forum seeks to emphasize the working of
non-political channels toward understanding in the region.
</P>
<P>
It also seeks to launch a dialogue on sustainable development
in southeastern Europe, to improve the image of the region and
promote the role of non-governmental organizations and society.
</P>
<P>
The organizers of the conference plan to discuss the issues on
the Internet.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the forum will include women working in the
fields of public opinion as well as the wives of the political
elite in Balkan countries.
</P>
<P>
The wives of the presidents of Macedonia, Romania and Albania,
and of the prime ministers of Turkey and Greece have confirmed
their participation.
</P>
<P>
Bulgarian Foreign Minister Nadezhda Mihailova, world-famous
Bulgarian opera singer Raina Kabaivanska, and jazz singer Jildaz
Ibrahimova are also expected at the forum.
</P>
<P>
The forum, which plans to adopt a final document that will be
presented to the political elite of southeastern Europe, wants to
create a women's network for sustainable development in the region
and convene on a regular basis, the report said. 
</P>
