- - - -
</P>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian industrial
output will drop 0.6 percent this year because of the economic
chaos caused by the international financial crisis, the press here
said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The same source said that the conclusion was arrived at by the
Brazilian Geography and Statistics Institute (IBGE) after its
monthly survey on the industrial sector. (Brazil-Industry)
</P>
<P>
