<HEADLINE> India's Ready-Made Garment Exports Show Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- India's ready-made garment
exports registered a moderate growth during the first eight months
of the current year compared with those recorded during the
corresponding period last year, official sources said here Friday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 913.5 million pieces valued at 3.41 billion U.S.
dollars were exported during January-August this year while 855.5
million pieces valued at 3.19 billion dollars were exported during
the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
The exports increased by 6.36 percent in volume and 6.84
percent in U.S. dollar terms this year. For fiscal 1998-99 (April
1, 1998-March 31, 1999), exports of ready-made garments covered
34.66 percent of the 5.9 billion dollars target set for the entire
fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
India has set the export target for ready-made garments 20
percent higher than last fiscal year's exports of 4.91 billion
dollars.
</P>
<P>
Exports to the United States rose by 12.26 percent in quantity
terms and 12.53 percent in value terms during January-August as
compared with the corresponding figures the year before. Shipments
to the European Union accounted for 414 million pieces and were
worth 1.2 billion dollars registering a 7.17-percent increase in
quantity and 4.29 percent in value terms. 
</P>
</TEXT>
