<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0252 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People's Parliament Formed in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 18 (Xinhua) -- A People's Parliament Elected
in the 1990 Multi-Party General Election of Myanmar was formed
unilaterally here Thursday, according to an announcement of the
Representing Committee of the Parliament Elected in the Election
(RCPEE) available here Friday.
</P>
<P>
The RCPEE, at its first meeting held Thursday, elected U Saw
Mya Aung, chairman of the Rakhine League for Democracy (RLD),
chairman of the parliament.
</P>
<P>
The duration of the parliament will last until a state
constitution is prescribed by it, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The convening of the parliament was supported by organizations
including four ethnic armed groups of Shan, Kayin, Kayan and Mon,
three of which have already made peace with the present military
government, the State Peace and Development Council (SPDC), it
said.
</P>
<P>
It also stated that all laws, decrees, orders and directives
issued since September 18, 1988, when the former military
government, the State Law and Order Restoration Council (SLORC)
took over the power of state, shall be unlawful until approval by
the People's Parliament.
</P>
<P>
The resolution of the RCPEE meeting demanded unconditional
release of all political prisoners.
</P>
<P>
It called on the Armed Forces to protect the state and the
people, safeguard the constitution and carry out purely the
national defense duty, upholding people's desire.
</P>
<P>
The RCPEE will work for the successful convening of a People's
Parliament Elected in the 1990 Election, the announcement added.
</P>
<P>
The 10-member RCPEE was formed Wednesday with Chairman of the
National League for Democracy (NLD) U Aung Shwe as its chairman, U
Than Tun and U Aye Tha Aung as secretaries. Other members include
U Tin Oo, NLD vice-chairman, and Aung San Suu Kyi, NLD general
secretary.
</P>
<P>
So far, the SPDC has no reaction upon the announcement of the
RCPEE.
</P>
<P>
In the 1990 general election, participated in by 93 political
parties, the NLD won 396 out of the 485 parliamentary seats.
</P>
<P>
But no parliament has emerged since the end of the election,
the RCPEE announcement said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
