<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Trains to Run Faster </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Trains operated by the
Shanghai Railway Administration will run faster and more trains
will be put into service on October 1.
</P>
<P>
The speed for trains will be marginally increased on the
Tianjin-Pukou, Shanghai-Nanjing and Shanghai-Hangzhou trunk lines.
</P>
<P>
Trains on the Beijing-Shanghai Railway will operate at speeds
between 130-160 km/hr, with the travel time between the two cities
reduced by an average 68 minutes. Travel time between Shanghai and
Kowloon will be reduced by 75 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The number of express, tourist and daily return-trip trains
will be increased and will ensure that a train will either arrive
or depart the Shanghai Railway Station every 20 to 30
minutes. 
</P>
