<HEADLINE> Kings Name Eighth Coach Since 1985 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Rick Adelman signed as
the head coach of the NBA Sacramento Kings on Thursday in
Sadramento, California, news reports said.
</P>
<P>
This is the eighth head coach for the Kings since 1985 and the
team hopes Adelman can repeat his feat that helped Portland to
the NBA Finals twice.
</P>
<P>
"With my experience and with a good staff, we can make
something happen here," Adelman was quoted as saying. "There's a
young group of players here that can only get better."
</P>
<P>
The Kings have not had a winning season since moving to
Sacramento in 1985. The coaching post has heen vacant since
August 18, when the team fired Eddie Jordan, who left with a
33-64 career record. Adelman said he will begin an immediate
search for a coaching staff.
</P>
<P>
"Everybody I've coached I tell him, whatever their history,
we start today," Adelman said. "I'm usually very up front with
them. And I find that players respond to that. Most players want
to feel not only can the team succeed but can you help me succeed
too."
</P>
<P>
Adelman has a 357-252 record in six seasons with Portland and
Golden State. He had two seasons left on a four-year,
4-million-dollar contract with Golden State when he was fired
after the 1997 season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
