<HEADLINE> Brazilian Industrial Output to Drop 0.6 Percent in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Brazilian industrial
output will drop 0.6 percent this year because of the economic
chaos caused by the international financial crisis, the press here
said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The same source said that the conclusion was arrived at by the
Brazilian Geography and Statistics Institute (IBGE) after its
monthly survey on the industrial sector.
</P>
<P>
Industrial output accumulated from January to July of this year
registered a 0.5 percent drop, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
Myriam Thereza Ferreira, who conducted the survey, said that an
important cut in the coming months could make the situation even
worse.
</P>
<P>
The institute had estimated that the industrial sector could
grow this year one or two percent.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian industrial production registered last year a 3.9
percent growth, said the IBGE. 
</P>
