<HEADLINE> Liaoning Reports Stable Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Officials statistics
indicate that northeast China's Liaoning Province has recorded
steady economic development through January-August 1998.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning's gross domestic product (GDP) for the first eight
months of the year hit 203.5 billion yuan (24.5 billion US
dollars), up seven percent on the 1997 period.
</P>
<P>
The incremental value of the agricultural sector rose by nine
percent during the period, with the industrial sector growing by
6.5 percent and the service sector by 7.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Vice Governor Guo Tingbiao said that Liaoning will strengthen
reforms between now and the end of the year in order to achieve
the 1998 economic growth rate of eight percent.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning's budgeted revenue for the eight month period stood at
13.98 billion yuan, a level representing real term growth of 9.4
percent. 
</P>
