<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Tamil Rebel Leader Arrested in Canada </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 19 (Xinhua) -- Members of the Royal Canadian
Mounted Police (RCMP) and the Toronto Service Tamil Task Force
have recently arrested a Sri Lankan Tamil rebel leader, according
to reports reaching here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Muralitharan Nadarajah, a leader of the Liberation Tigers of
Tamil Eelam (LTTE) has been charged with impersonation,
obstruction of justice and having false documents and functions in
Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
He was under investigation by the RCMP Militant Immigration and
Passport section for allegedly being in Canada under false
identification and for his alleged leadership role in LTTE
activities in Switzerland.
</P>
<P>
Nadarajah was produced before the Scarborough Court on
September 16.
</P>
<P>
In Switzerland, he had been arrested with 16 LTTE activists in
1996 for being the organizer of a criminal organization extorting
money from Tamils. He was later released on bail pending further
investigation.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a civil war against the Sri Lankan
government since 1983 for a separate state in the country.
</P>
