</P>
<P>
Asahi, Mainichi:
</P>
<P>
-- Japan's ruling Liberal Democratic Party and opposition
parties have agreed on temporary nationalization of the ailing
Long-Term Credit Bank of Japan.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Yomiuri, Mainichi:
</P>
<P>
-- Masahiro Akiyama, administrative vice minister of Japan's
Defense Agency, admitted Thursday that officials of the agency's
scandal-tainted procurement department moved and destroyed
documents in a bid to hide them from prosecutors investigating
alleged contract irregularities.
</P>
<P>
Asahi, Yomiuri, Nihon Keizai:
</P>
<P>
-- The Nikkei stock index fell to a more than 12-year closing
low Thursday, as government efforts to fix the Long-Term Credit
Bank of Japan failed to erase overall fears about Japan's ailing
financial system and the weakening economy. 
