<HEADLINE> Anhui to Increase Funding for Infrastructure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HEFEI, September 18 (Xinhua) -- East China's Anhui Province
plans to spend an additional 26 billion yuan to refurbish
infrastructure facilities damaged during summer flooding.
</P>
<P>
Anhui Governor Hui Liangyu said the province will invest 11
billion yuan in related projects during 1998 to boost its annual
GDP by one percentage point.
</P>
<P>
Anhui will allocate special funding totalling 2.01 billion yuan
for water conservancy projects, including a projects along
tributaries and the mainstream of the Huaihe River.
</P>
<P>
The Development Bank of China will provide loans totalling 9.1
billion yuan over the next 3-5 years for key highways, including
the Anhui Section of the Shanghai-Chongqing Expressway and the
Hefei-Hangzhou Expressway. The Ministry of Railways will allocate
an additional one billion yuan to double-track the Huainan and
Wan-Gan railways.
</P>
<P>
Anhui plans to spend seven billion yuan to upgrade rural power
grids, and will spend 2.91 billion yuan to upgrade grids in 70
counties during 1998 alone.
</P>
<P>
Anhui will also strengthen water supply, sewage treatment and
road construction projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
