<HEADLINE> Hunan Officials Arrested for Illegal Logging </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Three rural officials in
central China's Hunan Province were recently arrested on charges
related to illegal logging.
</P>
<P>
The trio, which includes former Party and government leaders in
from a Chenzhou township, allegedly printed and issued logging permits
which have led to destruction of some 85 hectares of trees along
the Yangtze River since March this year.
</P>
<P>
The officials face criminal prosecution are expected to receive
minimum prison sentences of seven years, according to
knowledgeable sources.
</P>
<P>
Deforestation has been cited as one of the main factors
contributing to heavy summer flooding, the worst in many
decades. The government has pledged to intensify the battle
against illegal logging and launch a massive nationwide
afforestation program. 
</P>
