<HEADLINE> Australia's Beashel Retains Lead at World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Australian Colin Beashel
regained his lead at the Star world championship with a third
place finish in Portoroz, Slovenia, on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Beashel and crewmate David Giles extended their lead over
Germany's Alexander Hagen to 13 points with two races to go.
</P>
<P>
American pair Mark Neeleman and Jos Schriers won Thursday's
race which was held in very difficult conditions, ranging from
virtually no wind to nearly 30 knots.
</P>
<P>
Mark Reynolds and Magnus Liljedahl, who recently won the
European Championships, were second, but after being disqualified
for a premature start in race two, were way down the leaderboard.
</P>
<P>
The world championshipsalso serves as qualifying event for the
2000 Olympic Games in Sydney. 
</P>
</TEXT>
