<HEADLINE> Jakarta's High-rise Buildings Urged to Check Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 18 (Xinhua) -- The management of high-rise
buildings in Jakarta are urged to keep their buildings fire-proof,
since the existing fire fighters cannot possibly handle too many
fires all by themselves.
</P>
<P>
"You cannot count on us too much because the Jakarta fire
fighting service is not able to control all of the fires," chief
of the Jakarta fire fighting authorities H. Suharso was quoted by
Antara News Agency Friday as saying.
</P>
<P>
When asked if it was necessary for a regular inspection of the
readiness of high-rise buildings in coping with a fire, Suharso
said that it is quite a remote possibility.
</P>
<P>
The local government has very limited capacity in fire fighting
because of inadequate equipment and resources.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, Suharso urged the management of high-rise buildings
to conduct their own inspection on a weekly or monthly basis.
</P>
<P>
According to him, only 389 of the 864 existing high-rise
buildings in Jakarta are adequately equipped for fire fighting.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that in 1997 a total of 84,629 fires broke out
in Jakarta, and 764 fires this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
