<DOCNO> XIE19980918.0291 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-18 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Asia's Largest Gas Purification Project Launched in Shaanxi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 18 (Xinhua) -- Asia's largest natural gas
purification factory went into operation recently in Jingbian
County, Shaanxi Province in northwest China.
</P>
<P>
As part of the Changqing gas field in northern Shaanxi, the
facility has a designed capacity to purify three billion cubic
meters of natural gas a year. With verified reserves of 130
billion cubic meters, the field is one of the largest in the world.
</P>
<P>
The plant is expected to pipe 1.5 billion cubic meters of
purified natural gas a year to Beijing, Tianjin, Xi'an and Yinchuan,
and has already begun sending gas to Beijing and Xi'an.
</P>
<P>
In line with the standards set by the state authorities, gas
produced by the Changqing field must be purified before being sent
to consumers.
</P>
<P>
The project is expected to further alleviate air pollution
in large cities such as Beijing, Tianjin and Xi'an. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
