<HEADLINE> Bugno Claims Convincing Win at Tour of Spain 12th Stage </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Italian Gianni Bugno claims a
convincing win on the 12th stage of the Tour of Spain on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He broke away in the final third of the 187 kilometers stage
from Benasque to Canfranc. Spain's Santi Blanco finished second,
one minute 48 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
The main pack, which included race leader Abraham Olano of
Spain, were more than nine minutes behind Bugno.
</P>
<P>
Olano was still the first overall because none of the eight
riders ahead of him were a threat. 
