<HEADLINE> Mantilla, Costa Advance in Bournemouth Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Felix Mantilla and
Albert Costa both advanced into the quarterfinals of the
Bournemouth Open on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Third seed Mantilla, the defending champion, beat fellow
Spaniard Jordi Burillo 7-5, 6-2 while 1996 winner Costa defeated
Dennis van Scheppingen of the Netherlands 6-3, 6-2.
</P>
<P>
Mantilla finished strongly after a tight first set against
Burillo, ranked 88 places below Mantilla at 110th in the world.
In the second set Burillo saved a match point in the final game
but was beaten in the next rally.
</P>
<P>
Second seed Costa was 3-2 and a break of serve behind against
Van Scheppingen before turning the match with a run of seven
games.
</P>
<P>
Costa next plays the eighth-seeded Frenchman Arnaud Clement
and Mantilla takes on Austrian Stefan Koubek. 
