<HEADLINE> Afghan Taliban Capture Strategic Sheber Pass: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Afghan Taliban militia
captured a strategic pass Thursday from the opposition Northern
Alliance in central Afghanistan, a report Radio Shariat said.
</P>
<P>
After two days of heavy fighting, the Taliban advanced on the
strategic Sheber Pass from the central province of Bamyan and
joined up with another force in the adjacent Ghorband Valley
further east, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Radio Shariat as saying that "in its
operation, the mujahideen of the Islamic emirate cleaned up vast
areas around Sheber and inflicted heavy losses on the enemy."
</P>
<P>
Ghorband cuts off Bamyan from Parwan province which is still
held by former Afghan defense minister Ahmadshah Masood.
</P>
<P>
It is believed that the Taliban will continue through Ghorband
Valley to attack forces loyal to Masood on its eastern flank,
putting pressure on his troops in Parwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
