<HEADLINE> Norwegian General Named as Head of UN Force in Macedonia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Brigadier-General Ove
Johnny Stromberg of Norway had been named as head of the United
Nations Preventive Force (UNPREDEP) in the former Yugoslav
Republic of Macedonia, U.N. spokesman Fred Eckhard said here on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He will succeed Brigade-General Bent Sohnemann of Denmark on
September 30, 1998.
</P>
<P>
UNPREDEP, which consists of 716 members, was deployed in 1992
to deter the spread of fighting in other parts of the former
Yugoslavia to Macedonia.
</P>
<P>
Despite plans to withdraw the force earlier this year, its
mandate was extended because of the volatile situation in the
neighbouring Serbian province Kosovo, where the ethnic Albanian
majority wants independence from Yugoslavia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
