<HEADLINE> Third Suspect in U.S. Embassy Bombing Charged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. federal complaint
said here Thursday that Hroun Fazil from the Comoro Islands was
the third suspect in the August bombing of the U.S. embassy in
Kenya.
</P>
<P>
The man in his mid-20s helped conspire the bombing and rented a
Nairobi villa for three months prior to the incident to make the
bomb, the complaint said.
</P>
<P>
On the day of the bombing, Fazil who has remained at large,
drove a white pickup truck to the U.S. embassy in Nairobi, with
another vehicle carrying the bomb following, it added.
</P>
<P>
Like the other two suspects who the U.S. Federal Bureau of
Investigation brought here last month for trial, Fazil was charged
with murder, murder conspiracy and conspiracy to use weapons of
mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
The bombing killed more than 250 people including 12 Americans
and injured over 5,000.
</P>
<P>
The first two suspects, named Mohamed Sadeek Odeh and Mohamed
Rashed Daoud Al-'Owhali, are being held in New York. 
</P>
</TEXT>
