<HEADLINE> Expert: Greece Has About 80,000 Drug Users </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- There were some 80,000 drug
addicts in Greece and the number of drug users aged under 18 rose
about 15 percent in the 1994-1998 period, a Greek expert said
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference in the northern Greek city of
Thessaloniki, forensic scientist Mattheos Tsoungas said that the
age at which Greeks first try drugs was falling to as low as 10,
the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
<P>
In Thessaloniki alone, he said, there were 10,000 addicts and
there had been 30 drug-related deaths since the beginning of the
year.
</P>
<P>
He added that the figure of 30 drug-related deaths did not
include those addicts who died of aids or hepatitis or those
killed in road accidents while under the influence of drugs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
