<HEADLINE> Congo (K) Rebels Deny Arrest of Local Chiefs  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The rebels fighting
Congolese President Laurent Kabila have denied reports that they
Rwanda, Rwandan News Agency (RNA) reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted Radio Bukavu as saying that the military
command of south Kivu said this was mere propaganda aimed at
troubling peace and security of the residents.
</P>
<P>
The rebels said the "Bami" are well-off in their territories,
both in South and North Kivu, RNA said, in a special dispatch to
Xinhua based here.
</P>
<P>
The radio further said that no fighting is taking place at
Kalemie, and that key towns in the east and northeast of Congo
(K) like Kisangani, Lubutu, Shabunda, are in rebels' hands.
</P>
<P>
The rebels also claimed that they have encircled Kindu, the
capital of Maniema Province, which is considered an important
military base in the region.
</P>
<P>
The rebels are pushing toward Lubumbashi, and are meeting very
little resistance from Kabila's forces and their allies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
