<HEADLINE> Greece, U.S. Decide to Strengthen Police Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Greece and the United States
decided Thursday to promote a protocol for police cooperation in
order to better combat organized crime.
</P>
<P>
The decision came following a meeting between Greek Public
Order Minister George Romeos and Louis Freeh, director of the U.S.
Federal Bureau of Investigation (FBI).
</P>
<P>
The two men discussed ways of further strengthening bilateral
cooperation between the Greek police and the FBI.
</P>
<P>
Terrorism, money laundering, drug smuggling and illegal
immigration also dominated their talks.
</P>
<P>
Freeh arrived here Thursday for a two-day visit to Greece.
</P>
</TEXT>
